# Pre-built dive 0.13.1 is compiled with Go 1.24.1, which carries CVE-2025-68121
# (improper cert validation during TLS session resumption in crypto/tls).
# This is a real CVE in the Go stdlib, but unexercised by dive's code paths:
#   - dive is a local CLI; it does not open a TLS server with GetConfigForClient
#   - dive's only outbound calls are to the local Docker daemon over a Unix
#     socket (or DOCKER_HOST over plain TCP); no TLS session resumption surface
#   - the vulnerable Config.Clone mutation pattern is not present in dive
# Trivy reports the CVE because it scans the embedded Go stdlib in the binary,
# not because the binary actually exercises the bug.
# Upstream fix requires a new dive release built with Go >= 1.24.13.
# Last checked: 2026-06-04. Re-evaluate when dive ships a new release.
CVE-2025-68121
